Parvaty is still watching the tea boil. Prabha goes over to her.
PRABHA (CONT’D)
(softly so only she can hear)
I had a word with doctor Supriya. She has
spoken to her lawyer friend... He said he will
have a look at your case!
Not responding, Parvaty takes the tea off the stove.
PRABHA (CONT’D)
He won’t even charge a penny!
Parvaty pours the chai into small porcelain cups, not responding.
PRABHA (CONT’D)
I thought... I thought it would make you
happy.
Parvaty turns to Prabha. She puts her hands into her ochre sari blouse and takes
out a small newspaper packet. She unfurls it and it has some red herbal powder
inside. She scoops some into her mouth and start chewing it.
7.
8.
PARVATY
It won’t do much good..
(chewing)
Last night... the builders sent a goon to my
house, isn’t it? Rascal started to threaten me!
Prabha gasps.
